          <img
            src="/images/logos/Huggingface.svg"
            alt="huggingface logo"
            loading="lazy"
          />

          <img
            src="/images/logos/mcdonalds.svg"
            alt="mcdonalds logo"
            loading="lazy"
          />

          <img src="/images/logos/huma.svg" alt="huma logo" loading="lazy" />

          <img
            src="/images/logos/capital-one.svg"
            alt="capital-one logo"
            loading="lazy"
          />

          <img
            src="/images/logos/home/airbyte.svg"
            alt="airbyte logo"
            loading="lazy"
          />

          <img
            src="/images/logos/betterment.svg"
            alt="betterment logo"
            loading="lazy"
          />

          <img
            src="/images/logos/deutsche-telekom.svg"
            alt="Deutsche Telekom logo"
            loading="lazy"
          />

          <img src="/images/logos/kong.svg" alt="kong logo" loading="lazy" />
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-container flex-row-reverse container">
        <div>
          <h2>What's the difference between Metabase and Looker?</h2>
          <p>
            TL;DR Lots of people who have worked with Looker in the past now
            choose Metabase because you get similar outcomes at a <a
              href="/pricing/">fraction of the price</a
            >, without needing to know a proprietary modeling language. Metabase
            also has a lower learning curve and lets non-technical and
            less-data-savvy teammates query data with or without SQL.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <video
            class="vjs-player lazy w-100 pause-observer autoplay-video"
            autoplay=""
            muted=""
            playsinline=""
            poster="/images/landing-pages/drill-through.gif"
          >
            <source
              src="/images/landing-pages/drill-through.mp4"
              type="video/mp4"
            />

            <p class="vjs-no-js">
              To view this video please enable JavaScript and consider upgrading
              to a web browser that
              <a href="https://videojs.com/html5-video-support/" target="_blank"
                >supports HTML5 video</a
              >
            </p>
          </video>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-container container two-checklists">
        <div>
          <h2>What makes Metabase a good choice compared to Looker?</h2>
          <p></p>

          <ul class="checklist-outline">
            <li>
              <b>Easy for everyone to use.</b> Intuitive tools like <a
                href="/features/analytics-dashboards">interactive dashboards</a
              > with quick drill-through analyses, the <a
                href="/features/query-builder"
                >query builder to write questions without SQL</a
              >, and one-click-to-create charts.
            </li>

            <li>
              <b>Set up without any specialist skills or modeling languages.</b>
              Query and visualize your data source as soon as you add it. You don‚Äôt
              <i>have</i> to model it first - but you <i>can</i> with <a
                href="/features/models">intuitive model creation</a
              > that doesn‚Äôt take 6+ weeks to learn.
            </li>

            <li>
              <b>Open source and affordable.</b>
              <a href="/pricing/">Transparent pricing</a> for startups through to
              advanced functionality and support for Enterprise.
            </li>

            <li>
              <b
                >Super fast to set up and integrate with your favorite data
                tools, like dbt for modeling.</b
              > Go from install to creating your first dashboard in less than 5 minutes.
              No technical skills or data team required.
            </li>

            <li>
              <b>Interactive, customer-facing analytics in days, not sprints.</b
              >
              <a href="/product/embedded-analytics"
                >Customizable embedded analytics</a
              > that lets your customers explore their data with as much - or as
              little - flexibility as you want.
            </li>

            <li>
              <b>Help from our world-class Success team.</b> Technical experts who
              help with everything from troubleshooting to advice on best practices.
              Looker‚Äôs once raved about Department of Customer Love is no longer
              (raved about, nor exists) since they were acquired.
            </li>

            <li>
              <b>Private and secure.</b>
              <a href="/security">We never look at or copy your data</a>. And we
              prioritize privacy and security features to secure data access in
              your org, like SSO and fine-grained permissions.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2>When might Looker be a better fit than Metabase?*</h2>
          <p></p>

          <ul class="checklist-outline">
            <li>You‚Äôre LookML certified (or have access to someone who is).</li>

            <li>
              You need a lot of governance built into your business intelligence
              platform with advanced modeling for complex data relationships and
              calculations.
            </li>

            <li>You need a modeling layer strictly in code</li>

            <li>
              You only want <i>some</i> of your people querying your data.
            </li>

            <li>
              You‚Äôve always wanted to learn LookML and you‚Äôve got a fair bit of
              time to pick it up (think 6 weeks).
            </li>

            <li>
              You‚Äôre a technical team - or you‚Äôve got access to technical people
              with a decent amount of time - who can help with configuration and
              set up.
            </li>

            <li>You hang out exclusively in the Google Suite.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="testimonial">
        <p>
          <b>*For the record...</b> Metabase also supports a number of happy enterprise-level
          customers for all their BI needs - and for some, just the self-service
          analytics part in addition to tools like Looker. Metabase also offers integration
          with a broad range of tools like dbt for semantic layering. (We‚Äôre trying
          to present a somewhat balanced view here, but c‚Äômon, it‚Äôs still our website
          üòè)
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="testimonial">
        <p>
          ‚Äú<a href="/case-studies/floryn"
            >Metabase costs us roughly one third of the cost of our previous BI
            tool (Looker)</a
          > while simultaneously offering better visualizations and easier use.‚Äù
        </p>

        <p class="author">Tijs Bronnenberg</p>
        <p class="company">Business Analyst at Floryn</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-container">
        <h4 class="faq-headline">Frequently asked questions</h4>

        <div class="faq">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <div>When is Metabase a better choice than Looker?</div>
            <img alt="Chevron Blue" src="/images/chevron_blue.svg" width="14" />
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div>
              <p>
                Metabase is best suited for businesses that need a
                straightforward way for everyone in the team to self-serve
                analytics without having to rely too heavily on your data team.
                It's BI that your team will actually enjoy using, at the right
                price for your scale.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-question">
            <div>When is Looker a better choice than Metabase?</div>
            <img alt="Chevron Blue" src="/images/chevron_blue.svg" width="14" />
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div>
              <p>
                Credit where it‚Äôs due - Looker can be a good fit for very
                technical teams who need more extensive governance and modeling
                strictly in code, with a lower need for everyone in the org to
                be able to jump in and run their own reports. It‚Äôs got all the
                bells and whistles - and depending on the maturity of your org,
                your use case and needs, it may be more than you need.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-question">
            <div>Who uses Metabase over Looker?</div>
            <img alt="Chevron Blue" src="/images/chevron_blue.svg" width="14" />
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div>
              <p>
                Metabase is trusted by over 80,000 companies with their
                analytics, from startups who need their first business
                intelligence tool through to Enterprises. Metabase open source
                is the go-to choice for founders and solo-developers to let
                their teams get answers from data on their own so they‚Äôre not
                running the same reports once a month. Metabase Pro and
                Enterprise is generally chosen by CTOs, CPOs, Heads of Data who
                have been there, done that with every other BI tool on the
                market and need a way to make self-service analytics actually
                happen.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-question">
            <div>What use cases do Metabase and Looker cover?</div>
            <img alt="Chevron Blue" src="/images/chevron_blue.svg" width="14" />
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div>
              <p>
                Both Metabase and Looker cater to internal analytics, as well as
                interactive embedded analytics for customers.
              </p><p>
                Metabase is ideal for quick, intuitive data exploration that
                lets people in your company click around in interactive
                dashboard and visualizations to learn from data, or create
                queries with or without SQL.
              </p><p>
                Looker may be better suited for complex data analysis and
                putting detailed visualizations in front of customers.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-question">
            <div>
              What‚Äôs the difference in pricing between Metabase and Looker?
            </div>
            <img alt="Chevron Blue" src="/images/chevron_blue.svg" width="14" />
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div>
              <p>
                Metabase is open source with affordable plans available for
                additional security and governance features, cloud deployment,
                and fast, unlimited technical help from engineers.
              </p><p>
                Looker's pricing is generally higher with user-based licensing
                with various pricing tiers depending on the use case.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-question">
            <div>Do you need to know SQL to use Metabase and Looker?</div>
            <img alt="Chevron Blue" src="/images/chevron_blue.svg" width="14" />
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div>
              <p>
                Metabase and Looker both let data analysts work in SQL; and less
                technically savvy people ask questions without SQL. Metabase's
                intuitive Query Builder lets non-technical or data savvy people
                put together analyses with clicks - no SQL necessary. Analysts
                and data people who prefer to write SQL can fill their boots in
                the SQL editor.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-question">
            <div>
              How do Metabase and Looker compare in terms of visualization
              capabilities?
            </div>
            <img alt="Chevron Blue" src="/images/chevron_blue.svg" width="14" />
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div>
              <p>
                Metabase and Looker give people a way to visualize their data
                and make sense of the numbers. But Metabase is so much more than
                just a visualization tool. For people who feel like they‚Äôre
                seeing double when staring at columns, it‚Äôs an intuitive way to
                filter and summarize to uncover trends and get insights to make
                data-driven decisions.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-question">
            <div>
              Ok, give it to me straight though - what‚Äôs the best Business
              Intelligence tool?
            </div>
            <img alt="Chevron Blue" src="/images/chevron_blue.svg" width="14" />
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div>
              <p>
                There‚Äôs no right or wrong answers here. It will generally depend
                on your use case, how much you want people to be able to learn
                from data and run reports on their own without depending on your
                data team; your preferred data stack, how fast you need to get
                up and running, your budget, and more.
